    <note>Zhang(2) Dexiang [344] His ancestors lived in Quanzhou. His great-great grandfather moved to Pucheng and served Min as prefect of Jianning. His collateral descendants moved to Suzhou, Wuxian and established two lineages (zu). He was collateral kin of the same generation of Zhang(2) Dun's [333] grandfather and of Jie(3)'s [345] grandfather, Pin [342]. Dexiang was Li(2) Shangqing's [7040] father-in-law. His son-in-law's father was Li(2) Zhaoshu [987]. Dexiang recommended Huang(2) Yan's [865] (qv.) father, Ting [3419], for an initial appointment as Wuxian sheriff in 1023-30. Ting retired and moved his family to Suzhou, Wuxian. XCB, 98.1a; Suzhou FZ, 77.19a; Song Qi, WJ, 59.1a-7b. CBD, 3, 2094-5.</note>
